S1 21:27:57  NOTICE CCitizen :Restrictions: logged in, not Chair (4unavailable)
S1 21:27:57  NOTICE CCitizen :When prompted, cast a vote by typing /msg sb Y to vote yes, /msg sb N to vote no, or /msg sb A to abstain. The bot will respond with a confirmation that your vote was recorded. This may take a few seconds if there is high traffic volume.
S1 21:27:57  NOTICE CCitizen :The bot's response will include a 5-character code. If you choose, you can use this code to verify the integrity of our voting process. When results are published (immediately for some votes, after a web and telephone voting period for others), check for the following:
S1 21:27:57  NOTICE CCitizen :1. Your member ID is on the voters list if you voted, or isn't if you didn't vote.
S1 21:27:57  NOTICE CCitizen :2. Your key is associated with the correct vote.
S1 21:27:57  NOTICE CCitizen :3. The total number of votes equals the number of member IDs, and all sums are correct.
S1 21:27:57  NOTICE CCitizen :If there are any irregularities, the vote may have been tampered with.

Stenobot does not accept direct commands.
S1 22:16:23  NOTICE Levisan :sb is a second login used by Stenobot, protecting the bot from interference when communicating in the channel and making commands shorter for users interfacing directly with it. It provides the direct command interface on behalf of Stenobot.
S1 22:16:23  NOTICE Levisan :The following commands are used by normal users to interact with the bot. For information on a particular command, type /msg sb HELP command. For a list of commands applicable only to the Chair, type /msg sb HELP ADVANCED.
